<?xml version="1.0"?>
<xar:template xmlns:xar="http://xaraya.com/2004/blocklayout">
    <!-- Initialization of some information -->
    <xar:set name="mlsmode">
        <xar:var scope="config" name="Site.MLS.MLSMode" />
    </xar:set>
    <xar:set name="single_checked">false</xar:set>
    <xar:if condition="$mlsmode eq 'SINGLE'">
        <xar:set name="single_checked">true</xar:set>
    </xar:if>
    <xar:set name="boxed_checked">false</xar:set>
    <xar:if condition="$mlsmode eq 'BOXED'">
        <xar:set name="boxed_checked">true</xar:set>
    </xar:if>
    <xar:set name="unboxed_checked">false</xar:set>
    <xar:if condition="$mlsmode eq 'UNBOXED'">
        <xar:set name="unboxed_checked">true</xar:set>
    </xar:if>
    <fieldset>
        <legend>Mode of Operation</legend>
        <p>The multilanguage system (MLS) works in three different modes.</p>
        <p>Please note that you cannot use UNBOXED mode of the MultiLanguage system unless you have
        php 4.3.0 with the mbstring extension compiled in.</p>
        <div class="xar-form-input-wrapper">
            <xar:if condition="$single_checked">
                <input type="radio" id="mlsmode_single" name="mlsmode" value="SINGLE"
                checked="checked" />
            <xar:else/>
                <input type="radio" id="mlsmode_single" name="mlsmode" value="SINGLE" />
            </xar:if>
            <label for="mlsmode_single">Single Language Mode (SINGLE)</label>
        </div>
        <p>MLS uses only one character set, typically single byte but potentially multi byte if
        mb_string is built in. All information is stored coherently with the chosen character set
        (at installation time), and also user data is meaningful in the chosen character set.</p>
        <div class="xar-form-input-wrapper">
            <xar:if condition="$boxed_checked">
                <input type="radio" id="mlsmode_boxed" name="mlsmode" value="BOXED"
                checked="checked" />
            <xar:else/>
                <input type="radio" id="mlsmode_boxed" name="mlsmode" value="BOXED" />
            </xar:if>
            <label for="mlsmode_boxed">Per Page Mode (BOXED)</label>
        </div>
        <p>MLS can use more than one character set in the site (the same consideration for the
        single or multi byte matter as above can be applied here), but only one character set per
        page is used (this is an obvious concept maybe, but important to understand). Due to this
        fact content cannot be shared across through different language areas (for example an
        Arabic comment won't be shown in the English area even if they are referring to the same
        object, e.g. an article available in both English and Arabic). Another point is that every
        operation involves only a single language. This mode can produce unexpected results if
        mb_string is not installed.</p>
        <p>
            <xar:if condition="function_exists('mb_strlen')">(It is installed on this server, so
            you can give this mode a try) 
            <xar:else />(WARNING: mb_string is NOT installed on this server, proceed with
            caution)</xar:if>
        </p>
        <div class="xar-form-input-wrapper">
            <xar:if condition="$unboxed_checked">
                <input type="radio" id="mlsmode_unboxed" name="mlsmode" value="UNBOXED" checked="checked"/>
                checked="checked" />
            <xar:else/>
                <input type="radio" id="mlsmode_unboxed" name="mlsmode" value="UNBOXED" />
            </xar:if>
            <label for="mlsmode_unboxed">Full Multilanguage (UNBOXED) (experimental!)</label>
        </div>
        <p>MLS uses an universal character set to represent everything (read: UTF-8). This
        guarantees that no conversion is needed for the content representation. Every page is
        always shown according to the user chosen language, but the page can contain texts in other
        languages (for example a French article and comments inside an English page).</p>
    </fieldset>
    <fieldset>
        <legend>Language/Locale Configuration</legend>
        <p>The following locales are available to this site:</p>
        <xar:loop name="$locales">
            <div class="xar-form-input-wrapper-after">
                <xar:if condition="$loop:item['active'] eq 'true'">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="locale_#$loop:index#" name="active[]"
                    value="#$loop:item['name']#" checked="checked" />
                    <xar:else />
                    <input type="checkbox" id="locale_#$loop:index#" name="active[]"
                    value="#$loop:item['name']#" />
                </xar:if>
                <label for="locale_#$loop:index#">#$loop:item['name']#</label>
            </div>
        </xar:loop>
        <div class="xar-form-input-wrapper">
            <label for="defaultlocale" title="#xarML('Default locale to load')#"
            class="xar-form-label">Default Locale:</label>
            <select name="defaultlocale" id="defaultlocale">
                <xar:loop name="$locales">
                    <xar:if condition="xarMLSGetSiteLocale() eq $loop:item['name']">
                        <option value="#$loop:item['name']#" selected="selected">
                        #$loop:item['name']#</option>
                    <xar:else />
                        <option value="#$loop:item['name']#">#$loop:item['name']#</option>
                    </xar:if>
                </xar:loop>
            </select>
        </div>
    </fieldset>
    <input type="hidden" name="translationsbackend" id="translationsbackend" value="xml2php" />
